Text:
Searing Wind, Assault Wind, and now Heaven's Wind
and Chilled Wind...!
Damn monster...!

All our reinforcements are also First Children! How
have you managed to fight us for three days and
nights...?!
Ack...
But it looks like you've finally run out of magic...
You've been a real pain in my backside...!
Hyah!
Rejoice, I won't kill you just yet.
I'll torture you and your minions first.

Should I start with your arms first or your legs...?
Consider it a token of my gratitude.

Thanks to you, I've obtained both the key and Rose
Oriana.

If I play my cards right, I can outmaneuver Perv
Asshat and join the Rounds...
*gasp*
Oh...
Once again...
You've saved me!
What...?!

Impossible... Your arm, it's healed...no, grown
back... How?!
This is his...
...power!

Master Shadow...you are the moonlight that pierces
the darkness...
I am yours to do as you please with...

(While heading to the ruins to search for the
treasure, I sense people using magic and spot a
familiar-looking girl with strawberry hair who
looks like she's in a bit of trouble.)
(If I remember correctly, her name is Victoria.)

(I met her before when I was on one of my
cross-country strolls. She was possessed,
so I cured her, then left her with Alpha.)

(She was so timid she wouldn't hurt a fly back then,
so I'm kinda surprised to find her fighting for her
life while totally drenched in blood.)

(I can see she's in pain, so I heal her, but she
should still probably take it easier in the future.)
She's healed...
It's a miracle...
But what is he doing here...?
Are you okay?
Yes, sir!
Master Shadow, it's been a while.
...What happened here?

I made a mistake. The Cult of Diablos has already put
their plan into motion...

(A mistake, huh? It must be something she's too
embarrassed to tell anyone about. She was probably
doing something illegal, and the soldiers caught
her.)

(I'm impressed she was able to come up with that
cover story about the Cult of Diablos so quickly,
though.)
So, the treasure...I mean, ruins are up ahead.
I have a report on that matter.
It's about No. 666. The traitor.
(Is that some kinda employee number?)
She has betrayed the Shadow Garden.

No. 666 is unworthy of your grace, my lord.
I swear, I'll—
Wait, hold on!
Please, wait!
She was just trying to protect her mother—
As a result, the key was stolen.
...Huh?

Her transgressions are grave. The only way she can
atone is through death.
(Did she steal corporate secrets or something...?)
Death...?!
Seriously, what's your problem?!

You keep going on about that damn key! Is it so
important you'd trample on your own teammate's
feelings?!
That's need-to-know, and you don't need to know.

(I've had more than my fill of corporate intrigue for
now...)
Hm?
And she's no teammate of ours. Just a filthy traitor.

"Filthy"? Who the hell do you think you are?! You've
been hostile toward her from the start...

I don't recall giving a lowly minion like you
permission to run her mouth.
You know what? I've had it up to here with you—
Marriage...?
Master...Shadow...?
Rose is getting...married...?

(Plus, this guy she's marrying is her old fiancé, the
guy she already dumped. Why go back and marry
him now?)

Unbelievable... Then all of that...what was it for?
What was it all for?!

This is unacceptable...Rose Oriana...
Your betrayal...is absolutely...
...unacceptable!
Wha—? Huh? Why?!
I expected nothing less of you, my lord!
H-Hold on.
Wait.
May all be according to your will...
No...

Rose, I thought the whole reason you killed your dad
was so you could become the new monarch!
Why give up now and choose marriage...?

The existence of light is what makes darkness so
radiant...

If Rose becomes the monarch, my shadowbroker
play-acting will become that much cooler!
I'm coming for you, Rose Oriana!
